      • buildLogContent

        public java.lang.StringBuilder buildLogContent()
        This method generates a log object for each of the s*c*24*60 lines to be generated which would eventually be written into a file
        Returns:
        a string builder object which has s*c*24*60 lines separated by "\n" where 's' represents the number of servers, 'c' represents the number of cpus
